  <sharedProfiles>
    <profile name="Acts of Faith" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="8597-c126-833c-8a98">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">For each of your infantry units, after the last model in that unit dies, before removing it from the battlefield, that unit makes an ‘Act of Faith’ roll. To do so, roll 1 D6. If the result is 6, the roll is successful and all remaining attacks targeting that unit fail. Instead of dying and being removed from the battlefield, that unit Heals 2+D3 and becomes ready.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Choir of the Faithful (X”)" typeId="e9b6-89e0-ffee-5662" typeName="Ability" hidden="false" id="2fe1-71fb-63e5-c48d">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description:" typeId="22b9-735d-71b1-6d7a">While your infantry units are within 0+X” of one or more of your leader units, they gain the following ability:


Sisters’ Song: For each ranged attack that targets this unit, this unit gains Resilient 6+ for that attack.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
  </sharedProfiles>
  <sharedRules>
    <rule name="Holy Trinity" id="5328-f292-f3b4-de07" hidden="false">
      <description>For each attack made for this weapon, a Wound Roll of 6 for that attack causes an additional wound.</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
